<chapter version="1.2.0" number="9" name="Disappointing Answer">
  <summary>
    Back at the settlement, thriving in daily routines. Wellness checks still charming, mushroom paste still terrible. Then Elder Heartwood's answer arrives - and it's meaningless. Ancient tree can't comprehend individual human survival. Kira's reaction surprises everyone including herself: "Huh. Okay then." Not despair. Recognition that she already HAS her answer - this life, these friends. "Mav learned the Oracle was fake in Season 4. The journey was the real wisdom." The plants expect her to be devastated. She's... free?
  </summary>
  <focus>
    Disappointment handled with grace. "The journey was the answer all along" - literally an Uncharted episode. Found family realized. Freedom from waiting for authority. Kira already belongs here.
  </focus>
